textBeforeTable: The extractions for the Civil Parish of Kilgarrylander are within the present Catholic Parish of Keel, Castlemaine which lies west from Castlemaine village to and including Ballyarkane Eighter Townland (which is just east of Aughils), on both sides of the coastal road heading west from Castlemaine via Inch to Dingle Town on the Dingle Peninsula. Names are spelled as they were seen, but please note that those listed as Cormack are the same as O'Brien / Brien, and also Foley is seen as Folue, Foloua, and Tolue, Foulane, etc. Fraut is Trant, Toie could be Foley, Keary is Cary, Cournane/ Courtney, Ginnaw is McKenna, and Corkeran/Corheran is Corcoran, Neagle is Nagle, and Doody is probably Dowd.
